description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a fixed term post for 2 Years, due to Secondment Cover. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are an ABMU Health Board employee this post will only be offered on a secondment basis and you will need to have gained your line managers approval for the secondment prior to going to interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A vacancy has arisen for a suitably qualified and experienced specialist respiratory physiologist with experience to join our busy and expanding team working in the Respiratory Physiology unit at Morriston Hospital, Swansea.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Morriston provides specialist services to a population of approximately 1 million people distributed across south west and mid wales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The unit undertakes an extensive list of diagnostic and therapeutic procedures. Along with full lung function testing, these include the detailed assessment of sleep apnoea, Non-invasive ventilation and cardio-pulmonary exercise testing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to providing learning and development opportunities to all of our staff. We actively encourage and support all appropriate professional development in advanced respiratory investigations to facilitate individuals to reach their full potential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to expand your knowledge and experience and have the necessary qualifications and drive, why not rise to the challenge and look at a role in Morriston Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suitable candidates would hold a BSc.Clinical Physiology (Respiratory), STP MSc Respiratory Science or PTP BSc. Respiratory Science. Registration with RCCP or AHCS would be essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Simon Hilldrup&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Head of Respiratory Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Simon.Hilldrup@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01792703364&lt;/p&gt;
